Set Up Chat with a Guided Setup Flow

Get started with live web chat in Lightning Experience with a quick guided setup flow. Create a chat queue on Omni-Channel, select your chat team, and get the Embedded Service code snippet to add chat to your website.

The Chat setup flow is the fastest and easiest way to get up and running with live web chat. When you complete the flow, you’re ready to go online in the console and start chatting.

This setup flow sets up Chat for Lightning Experience. It also sets up Omni-Channel to route your chats and gets you started with Embedded Service.

In this setup flow, we walk you through:

* Setting up chat routing with Omni-Channel
* Specifying the website where you want customers to request a chat
* Selecting which records you want to link with your chats
* Creating an offline support form so your customers can log a case while your team is away
* Using the Embedded Chat code snippets to allow chat on your website

We also turn on several things in the background during the setup flow:

* Enabling Chat and Omni-Channel
* Creating a service channel for chats
* Basic Omni-Channel setup, including a queue enabled for chat and routing configuration
* Assigning Service Cloud User and Chat User licenses to users you select during the flow
* Creating presence statuses for your team to use
* Permission set with presence statuses assigned to users

We create a Chat deployment with default settings and a chat button, which is used to connect Chat to Embedded Service. We also create an Embedded Service deployment with default settings and branding selection.

If you don’t have an existing Experience Cloud or Salesforce site, we create one for you after providing the naming convention. We turn on guest access to the Support API on the Salesforce Site you select or create in the flow if you turn on Offline Support.

We add the Omni-Channel utility to your default Lightning Console app, allowing your agents to go online and accept incoming chat requests in Omni-Channel.

Learn where you can customize and view what you set up during the Chat setup flow.
title: Setup Chat with Salesforce Guided Flow
